ttp_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/topic/15060-wave-synth-sound-engine/#comment-102291_lt_/a_gt_\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t_lt_/div_gt_\n\n\t\t_lt_div class_eq__qt_ipsI_qt__gt__lt_/div_gt__lt_/div_gt_"},{"Owner":"Nesh108","Date":"2017-05-24T04:22:36Z","Content":"_lt_div class_eq__qt_mages_qt__gt_\n\t\t\t\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tHow about the _lt_a href_eq__qt_https_dd_//webaudio.github.io/web-midi-api/_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_https_dd_//webaudio.github.io/web-midi-api/_lt_/a_gt_? It sounds like it_t_s what we are looking for.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\t_lt_strong_gt_EDIT_dd_ _lt_/strong_gt_Here is a neat tutorial with demo included (_lt_a href_eq__qt_https_dd_//www.toptal.com/web/creating-browser-based-audio-applications-controlled-by-midi-hardware_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_https_dd_//www.toptal.com/web/creating-browser-based-audio-applications-controlled-by-midi-hardware_lt_/a_gt_) but it looks like it_t_s more about playing the MIDI via the web but the W3C specs also hinted on events from the MIDI device about the notes being played (_lt_a href_eq__qt_https_dd_//webaudio.github.io/web-midi-api/#MIDIMessageEvent_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_https_dd_//webaudio.github.io/web-midi-api/#MIDIMessageEvent_lt_/a_gt_).\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t_lt_/div_gt_\n\n\t\t_lt_div class_eq__qt_ipsI_qt__gt__lt_/div_gt__lt_/div_gt_"},{"Owner":"Wingnut","Date":"2017-05-24T11:30:36Z","Content":"_lt_div class_eq__qt_mages_qt__gt_\n\t\t\t\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tThanks guys... these look very interesting.  At least some folks are thinking about it_co_ eh?\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tUnfortunately_co_ there is no mention of MIDI in _lt_a href_eq__qt_https_dd_//www.w3.org/TR/html51/_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_the html5 spec_lt_/a_gt_.  Not that there SHOULD be... but... I think the audio element is not being considered AT ALL... for playing midi files.  That_t_s sad.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tThis probably means that only &lt_sm_embed&gt_sm_ and &lt_sm_object&gt_sm_ can play midi_co_ and they will hand-it-off to system... guided by the .mid mimetype to find a player.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tCompared to an .mp4 or .wav source for an &lt_sm_audio&gt_sm_ element... umm... I don_t_t know how it compares.  The &lt_sm_audio&gt_sm_ element seems to have quite a few limitations for the allowed file/mime types_co_ (.mid apparently isn_t_t one of them).  &lt_sm_audio&gt_sm_ probably uses a player built-into the browser_co_ or something like that. \n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\t_qt_Stream-audio_qt_ (samples) like .wav_co_ aiff_co_ mp3_co_ etc... don_t_t need access to the wavetables on the soundcard/on-board audio.  Only midi needs the wavetable... to get its instrument sounds.  hmm.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tThanks for the responses and research_co_ guys.  Reading reading reading.  _lt_img alt_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ data-emoticon_eq__qt__qt_ height_eq__qt_20_qt_ src_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/default_smile.png_qt_ srcset_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/smile@2x.png 2x_qt_ title_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ width_eq__qt_20_qt_ /_gt__lt_/p_gt_\n\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t_lt_/div_gt_\n\n\t\t_lt_div class_eq__qt_ipsI_qt__gt__lt_/div_gt__lt_/div_gt_"},{"Owner":"ozRocker","Date":"2017-05-24T22:24:06Z","Content":"_lt_div class_eq__qt_mages_qt__gt_\n\t\t\t_lt_p_gt_\n\tI_t_ve thought about this as well.  I_t_m also a musician_co_ performed over 100 shows in my life_co_ used to teach lead guitar.  What annoys me is having animations that don_t_t sync up to music.  I know its easier to sync MIDI cos of the sysex messages_co_ but I_t_d love to be able to sync MP3s according to certain frequencies (most likely bass)\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t_lt_/div_gt_\n\n\t\t_lt_div class_eq__qt_ipsI_qt__gt__lt_/div_gt__lt_/div_gt_"},{"Owner":"Wingnut","Date":"2017-05-24T23:05:16Z","Content":"_lt_div class_eq__qt_mages_qt__gt_\n\t\t\t\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tCool.  Yeah_co_ syncing the sampled-type audio would definitely be nice_co_ too.  I bet there_t_s more enthusiasm for THAT... than there is for listening-for-sysex from a midi player.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tPeople sort-of forgot about midi... but it won_t_t die.  The Chuck E. Cheese band will ALWAYS need it.  _lt_img alt_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ data-emoticon_eq__qt__qt_ height_eq__qt_20_qt_ src_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/default_smile.png_qt_ srcset_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/smile@2x.png 2x_qt_ title_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ width_eq__qt_20_qt_ /_gt__lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tThat thing that JcPalmer pointed-at... that was weird.  They send the midi file into a converter (pre-process into another file type)_co_ converter available live online_co_ and it converts to _lt_em_gt_something..._lt_/em_gt_ looked like _qt_blocks_qt_ of samplings.  Then they feed that into a JS synth_co_ which has no wavetables_co_ or maybe software based wavetables with a half-hour load-time.  And_co_ the embeded sysex messages could be lost along the way. \n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\t_qt_Faked_qt_ midi playback_co_ as Davrous puts it.  *nod*\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tCan you imagine how wonderful a midi timeline/eventScheduler would be?  Playground movies!  _lt_span_gt_2 hour run times... an entire war saga... red mesh vs blue mesh...  big orchestration... tunt... tuh tuh tuh tunt... _lt_/span_gt_marching into battle...tymps... swell... swell... SWELL...  CRESENDO!!!  Cannon fire.  _lt_img alt_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ data-emoticon_eq__qt__qt_ height_eq__qt_20_qt_ src_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/default_smile.png_qt_ srcset_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/smile@2x.png 2x_qt_ title_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ width_eq__qt_20_qt_ /_gt__lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tA six-stringer eh?  You probably play bass just fine_co_ too.  Likely some keys_co_ too.  Very cool.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tOnce upon a time_co_ I decided I would learn everything I could... about my Alesis s4 rack synth (a QuadraSynth without a keyboard).  The s4 is a wonderful sound module_co_ and by sending the right sysex at the right time (from a Cakewalk midi)... I learned to make that S4 SING!  _lt_img alt_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ data-emoticon_eq__qt__qt_ height_eq__qt_20_qt_ src_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/default_smile.png_qt_ srcset_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/smile@2x.png 2x_qt_ title_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ width_eq__qt_20_qt_ /_gt_ After some of my demented experiments were done_co_ I could hear that s4 panting and wheezing.  _lt_img alt_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ data-emoticon_eq__qt__qt_ height_eq__qt_20_qt_ src_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/default_smile.png_qt_ srcset_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/smile@2x.png 2x_qt_ title_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ width_eq__qt_20_qt_ /_gt_  Check this mess out...  _lt_a href_eq__qt_http_dd_//webpages.charter.net/wingthing/html/s4/s4sysex_p08.txt_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_http_dd_//webpages.charter.net/wingthing/html/s4/s4sysex_p08.txt_lt_/a_gt_\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tWhat kind of idiot... would make such a... ahh nevermind.  We music tards are a little _qt_off_qt_... you know well.  _lt_img alt_eq__qt__dd_D_qt_ data-emoticon_eq__qt__qt_ height_eq__qt_20_qt_ src_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/default_biggrin.png_qt_ srcset_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/biggrin@2x.png 2x_qt_ title_eq__qt__dd_D_qt_ width_eq__qt_20_qt_ /_gt__lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tYeah_co_ keeping motion in-sync with music... most people still HAVE TO render to video.  What fun is that?  The gamepad doesn_t_t work during play!  heh\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t_lt_/div_gt_\n\n\t\t_lt_div class_eq__qt_ipsI_qt__gt__lt_/div_gt__lt_/div_gt_"},{"Owner":"sssurikov","Date":"2017-08-26T15:43:21Z","Content":"_lt_div class_eq__qt_mages_qt__gt_\n\t\t\t\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tThere are no technical problem with synchronisation of scene events and sound. You don_t_t need MIDI API for this task at all.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tLook to _lt_a href_eq__qt_http_dd_//tinyurl.com/yasvy3t9_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_http_dd_//tinyurl.com/yasvy3t9_lt_/a_gt__lt_br /_gt_\n\tMore examples here_lt_br /_gt__lt_a href_eq__qt_https_dd_//surikov.github.io/riffshare/tools.html_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_https_dd_//surikov.github.io/riffshare/tools.html_lt_/a_gt_\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tIt sounds fine_co_ it looks nice._lt_br /_gt_\n\tIt uses WebAudioFont (see _lt_a href_eq__qt_https_dd_//www.npmjs.com/package/webaudiofont_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_https_dd_//www.npmjs.com/package/webaudiofont_lt_/a_gt_)\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tBut you should be musician to synchronise music pieces and actions in game. This is absolutly different task. \n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tYou binds sound effects to scene events in ordinal games._lt_br /_gt_\n\tIn your case_co_ on the contrary_co_ You should bind game events to musical events.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\t_lt_br /_gt_\n\tFeel free to ask any help to solve any problem in this area.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tP.S._lt_br /_gt_\n\tI don_t_t support SSSynthesiser anymore. Look to WebAudioFont. It has about 1000 instruments and drums_co_ equalizer_co_ reverberator etc.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\t \n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt__lt_a href_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/monthly_2017_08/sp320opt.gif.e057a6b086783cc9172a6e10307102b2.gif_qt_ class_eq__qt_ipsAttachLink ipsAttachLink_image_qt__gt__lt_img data-fileid_eq__qt_14595_qt_ src_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/monthly_2017_08/sp320opt.gif.e057a6b086783cc9172a6e10307102b2.gif_qt_ class_eq__qt_ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed_qt_ alt_eq__qt_sp320opt.gif_qt__gt__lt_/a_gt__lt_/p_gt_\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t_lt_/div_gt_\n\n\t\t_lt_div class_eq__qt_ipsI_qt__gt__lt_/div_gt__lt_/div_gt_"},{"Owner":"Wingnut","Date":"2017-08-26T16:29:26Z","Content":"_lt_div class_eq__qt_mages_qt__gt_\n\t\t\t\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tHey_co_ thanks for the reply and great examples.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tStill_co_ this feels like some kind of work-around.  The scene code would need to _qt_make_qt_ the calls to play the notes_co_ right?\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\t(perhaps I don_t_t understand real well - sorry)\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tIdeally_co_ in my fantasy_co_ midi is playing in a classic windows media player _qt_embed_qt_ (object or audio element)... and whatever midi player is being used_co_ it can be told to stream all noteON_co_ noteOFF_co_ and sysex events... at canvas.addEventListener(midiEvent_co_ _qt_onMidiEvent_qt_).\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tWouldn_t_t that be the cat_t_s meow?  (great)\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tSeeing that I sequenced (created) the midi song_co_ I would be the one inserting sysex/mmc/showControl messages in-between downbeats (I am a musician - rumor has it)... and inside my onMidiEvent()... if event.type _eq_ _qt_showControl_qt_... ahem ahem ahem.  _lt_img alt_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ data-emoticon_eq__qt__qt_ height_eq__qt_20_qt_ src_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/default_smile.png_qt_ srcset_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/smile@2x.png 2x_qt_ title_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ width_eq__qt_20_qt_ /_gt__lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tYou could do entire _qt_movies_qt_ made from a 2 hour midi song...  packed with music and show-control events_co_ using the wavetables built-into the sound cards.  The midi players are all running at hardware speeds_co_ and they would not bog our BJS scenes at all.  They are the boss.  They set the pace.  Our scene does nothing at all about playing notes.  It just listens.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tTHAT is what I would truly wish-for.  I don_t_t want to play any music with JS scene code.  Let the standard midi players - WMP_co_ winAmp_co_ bsPlayer_co_ whatever... do that for me_co_ and they ONLY send us midi events.  We_t_re not talking waves/samples here at all.  Just midi.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tSorry.  I hope I didn_t_t pee on the campfire.  I just don_t_t like having to play notes WITH scene code... if that is indeed what your demos are doing.  I prefer that the hardware-level midi players... just stream their stuff at our scene... so we can try to sync-up.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tActually not necessarily _qt_hardware-level_qt__co_ but _qt_system-level_qt_... stuff written in faster code... whatever Windows Media Player is coded-with.  _lt_img alt_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ data-emoticon_eq__qt__qt_ height_eq__qt_20_qt_ src_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/default_smile.png_qt_ srcset_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/smile@2x.png 2x_qt_ title_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ width_eq__qt_20_qt_ /_gt__lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tIn my experience with Windows and webcams_co_ I found that I needed to go through an _qt_activeX_qt_ thing... to get my camera to appear on a local webpage.  I have a feeling that the same thing is needed... to _qt_reach across Security Gulch_qt_ and connect to system midi players.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t_lt_/div_gt_\n\n\t\t_lt_div class_eq__qt_ipsI_qt__gt__lt_/div_gt__lt_/div_gt_"},{"Owner":"sssurikov","Date":"2017-08-26T18:12:05Z","Content":"_lt_div class_eq__qt_mages_qt__gt_\n\t\t\t\n_lt_blockquote class_eq__qt_ipsQuote_qt_ data-ipsquote_eq__qt__qt__gt_\n\t_lt_div class_eq__qt_ipsQuote_citation_qt__gt_\n\t\tQuote\n\t_lt_/div_gt_\n\n\t_lt_div class_eq__qt_ipsQuote_contents_qt__gt_\n\t\t_lt_p_gt_\n\t\t\t_lt_span style_eq__qt_background-color_dd_#ffffff_sm_color_dd_#353c41_sm_font-size_dd_14px_sm__qt__gt_The scene code would need to _qt_make_qt_ the calls to play the notes_co_ right?_lt_/span_gt_\n\t\t_lt_/p_gt_\n\t_lt_/div_gt_\n_lt_/blockquote_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tNo.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tScene should listen events of music player.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t_lt_/div_gt_\n\n\t\t_lt_div class_eq__qt_ipsI_qt__gt__lt_/div_gt__lt_/div_gt_"},{"Owner":